!!! 5
%html
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html;charset=utf-8", "http-equiv" => "Content-Type"}/
    %title Simple Atoms Model
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/modernizr/modernizr.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:type => "text/javascript"}
      if (!Modernizr.svg) { window.location = '../../browser-upgrade.html'; }
    %link{:href => "../examples.css", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}/
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/d3/d3.v2.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/jquery/jquery.min.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "../../vendor/science.js/science.v1.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "http://use.typekit.com/hdw8ayt.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:type => "text/javascript"}
      try{Typekit.load();}catch(e){}
    %link{:href => "http://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans:400italic,700italic,300italic,400,300,700&subset=latin,greek,latin-ext", :rel => "stylesheet", :type => "text/css"}/
  %body
    #header
      %a#logo(href="http://www.concord.org/")
        %img(src="../../resources/layout/cc-logo.png")
      %h1
        %a(href="http://lab.dev.concord.org/examples/simple-atoms-model/simple-atoms-model.html") Simple Atoms Model
      %img#fullscreen(class="size-full wp-image-1880" src="../../resources/layout/fullscreen.gif")
    #content
      #viz
        .top
          .square
            %img{:src => "../../resources/aspect-ratio-1x1.png"}
            #molecule-container
          .therm
            #thermometer
            #therm_text
        .bottom
          .component_group
            .slider_container
              Intermolecular Attraction
              .slider_content
                #attraction_slider
              .left_half
                weaker
              .right_half
                stronger
              .below
                Attractive Force
          .component_group
            .slider_container
              Force Interactions
              .slider_content
                Coulomb
                %input(id="coulomb-forces-checkbox" type="checkbox")
              .below
                %input(id="lennard-jones-forces-checkbox" type="checkbox" checked)
          .component_group
            .slider_container
              Change Temperature
              .content
                %div{:style=> "width: 10em; height: 2em; display: inline-block; margin: 0.5em"}
                  %button#cool_button(type="button" class="left_edge" value="colder")colder
                  %button#heat_button(type="button" class="right_edge" value="hotter")hotter

      #description-right
        %p
          A computational simulation of a collection of simple &ldquo;atoms&rdquo; which are free to move in two
          dimensions. The force between pairs of atoms is modeled using a
          <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lennard-Jones_potential" target="_blank">Lennard-Jones</a>
          potential.

        %p
          So that you can more easily explore how temperature and intermolecular attraction strength affect phase
          changes, intermolecular attractions are much stronger in this simulation than they are for the equivalent
          &ldquo;featureless&rdquo; and nonreactive atoms found in nature, those of the noble gases.

        %p
          When the Coulomb force interaction checkbox is checked, atoms also experience electrostatic interactions.
          Opposite charges of +1 or -1 are evenly distributed among the atoms, and then particles with opposite
          charge attract each other according to Coulomb's Law, while particles with the same charge repel.
          Particles with a positive charge appear blue and those with a negative charge appear red.

        %button{:id=>"save-button", :class=>"component button", :style=> "width: 5em; display: block"}
          Save
        #flash

    %script{:src => "../../lab/lab.js", :type => "text/javascript"}
    %script{:src => "application.js", :type => "text/javascript"}